<p>Status indicators</p><p>Understand the status indicators used through CORDAP. 
  </p> 
	 <p> 
		<p>Description</p> 
		<p> For many items throughout CORDAP,
		  colours are used to indicate the current status of an item. Items include
		  overall release, iterations, work packages, and resource allocation. The
		  following table describes the meanings of the colours used to indicate status. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		<table> 
		Status indicator colours 
		 
		   
		   
		   
		   
			  
				 
				   Colour 
				   
				 
				 
				   Status 
				   
				 
				 
				   Description 
				   
				 
			  
		   
		   
			  
				 
				   Green 
				   
				 
				 
				   On track 
				   
				 
				 
				  Based on remaining work and
					 the time left to complete the work, due date should be met. 
				   
				  >= 80%
					 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				   Yellow 
				   
				 
				 
				   Warning 
				   
				 
				 
				  Hours of remaining work is
					 slightly more than the working hours left until the due dateâ€”meeting the due
					 date is in jeopardy. 
				   
				   <
					 80% >= 65% 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Red 
				   
				 
				 
				  Critical 
				   
				 
				 
				   <
					 65% 
				   
				  Hours of remaining work is
					 significantly more than the working hours left until the due date. Expect the
					 completion of the work to be overdue. 
				   
				 
			  
		   
		 
		 
		</table> 
	 </p></p>